e American political system. The contributors include well-established names in law and political science, as well as up-and-coming scholars, offering a broad understanding of Bush v. Gore's long-term impact. This book will be useful as a classroom text in both survey courses on elections and the courts and for advanced courses that consider the impact of judicial rulings on the government and political process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aContested electionszUnited States. 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerzUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : Constitutional Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Electoral Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Law. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Presidency, The. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aAlthouse, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanks, Christopher P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanks, Christopher P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaugh, Joyce A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusch, Andrew E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, David B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, David B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGerber, Brian J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreco, Donald Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, John C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, John C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJones, Charles O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular